Rift Valley fever, Tanzania
-------------------------------
Information received on 12 Feb 2007 from Dr. Johnson O. Mollel,
Director of Veterinary Services, Veterinary Services, Ministry of
Livestock Development, Dar Es Salaam, Tanzania
Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date 18 Jan 2007
Date of confirmation of event 7 Feb 2007
Report date 12 Feb 2007
Date submitted to OIE 12 Feb 2007
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence July 1998
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent Rift Valley Fever Virus (Phlebovirus)
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (basic)
Report pertains to: Defined zone within the country
New Outbreaks. There were 6 new outbreaks reported on 18 Jan 2007 in
the region of Sale, Ngorongoro, Arusha. Each outbreak involved
cattle, sheep and goats with the largest number being 1800 cattle,
1290 sheep and 1370 goats in both the 1st and 2nd reported outbreak.
Individual outbreak information can be found at the OIE's WAHID
interface referenced above. We will present the summary data for all
6 outbreaks below.
Summary of outbreaks Total outbreaks: 6
Total animals affected
Species Cattle
Susceptible 4589
Cases 54
Deaths 32
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0
Species Sheep
Susceptible 5978
Cases 223
Deaths 144
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0
Species Goats
Susceptible 4447
Cases 170
