Slaughtered 0
Outbreak statistics
Species Cattle
Apparent morbidity rate 1.18 percent
Apparent mortality rate 0.70 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 59.26 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 0.70 percent
Species Sheep
Apparent morbidity rate 3.73 percent
Apparent mortality rate 2.41 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 64.57 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 2.41 percent
Species Goats
Apparent morbidity rate 3.82 percent
Apparent mortality rate 2.02 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 52.94 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 2.02 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction or slaughter
Epidemiology: Source of infection - Unknown or inconclusive; Airborne
spread; Vectors
Epidemiological comments: The affected area is on the floor of the
Rift valley and had higher than normal rains
Laboratory name and type Central Veterinary Laboratory Temeke
(National laboratory)
